Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addChannelDensityControl(25.10)                addChannelDensityControl(25.10)

Name
       addChannelDensityControl - Controls the routing density for a specified
       area  on  a  layer  by  setting a maximum density percentage that early
       Global Route cannot exceed

Syntax
       addChannelDensityControl

       [-help]

       <llx><lly><urx><ury><layer> <ratio>

       Controls the routing density for a specified area on a layer by setting
       a maximum density percentage that early Global Route cannot exceed. Use
       the addChannelDensityControl command after performing placement.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each addChannelDensityControl parameter. For a
              detailed description of the command and all of  its  parameters,
              use the man command

              man addChannelDensityControl.

       <layer>
              Specifies the layer on which to specify the routing density con-
              trol.

              Note:  Layers can be specified using the layer names or layer ID
              numbers.

              Data_type: string, required

       <llx>  Specifies the lower left x coordinate of the density area.

              Data_type: float, required

       <lly>  Specifies the lower left y coordinate of the density area.

              Data_type: float, required

       <ratio>
              Specifies the maximum routing density allowed for the area, as a
              percentage.

              Min: 0

              Max: 100

              Value: 0 (zero percent) to 1 (100 percent)

              Data_type: float, required

       <urx>  Specifies the upper right x coordinate of the density area.

              Data_type: float, required

       <ury>  Specifies the upper right y coordinate of the density area.

              Data_type: float, required

Examples
       The following command creates a routing density control area  on  layer
       Metal3 with a maximum density of 50 percent:

       addChannelDensityControl 10 10 500 30 Metal3 0.50

Related Information
              * setRouteMode

              * getRouteMode

              * Using  Early  Global  Route for Congestion and Timing Analysis
                chapter in the Innovus User Guide

